    "body": "In this Pull Request https://github.com/scikit-learn/scikit-learn/pull/3802 , around 0.5s out of 1.2s is spent in `check_pairwise_arrays` which is huge, because I call `pairwise_distances_argmin_min` repeatedly. \n1. There is dtype casting two times in `check_pairwise`to make sure X and Y are float, first is to convert it into a ndarray, and the second is to cast it into float. Should there be a `dtype` argument provided externally so that lines from https://github.com/scikit-learn/scikit-learn/blob/master/sklearn/metrics/pairwise.py#L98 to L104 can be removed.\n2. Should there be a `check_input=False` argument in the various metrics to avoid multiple checking of the input arrays? so that the user can override `check_pairwise_arrays`\n",
